        "content": "<p>Do people know the name of the dual property to disjointness? I'm introducing it in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/pull/14195\">#14195</a> under the name <code>codisjoint</code> (to match <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/disjoint\">docs#disjoint</a>), but I'm making the name up because I've never seen it in the literature.</p>",
        "id": 285025110,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1654417741
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"214703\">@Yury G. Kudryashov</span></p>",
        "id": 285025114,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1654417750
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Maybe \"exhaustive\"? <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collectively_exhaustive_events\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collectively_exhaustive_events</a></p>",
        "id": 285030709,
        "sender_full_name": "Bart Michels",
        "timestamp": 1654426585
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm... but this would go along with <code>exclusive</code>, not <code>disjoint</code>.</p>",
